posts.content:
Your sellers are losing time, but not always where you might think.
It's not just admin work. 


Look closer:

- Random internal emails
- Too many all-hands
- Cross-team "quick syncs"

That's exactly what(Enablement Leader of the Year - Seismic) discovered when her team assessed all emails hitting seller inboxes from cross-functional teams.

The solution? They "very politely shut them all down" and established a new rule:


- Enablement platform for key updates
- Monthly newsletter
- Teams channel for communication
- Clean inboxes for customers and management chain


The key? They proposed this communication strategy to senior leaders first, got approval, then executed.


Watch the full episode in comments to learn how enablement can lead organizational change

Salespeople‚Ä¶ This is the cold call framework I used to book hundreds of meetings last year. 



It goes like this.

Opener ‚Üí Probing question (or poking the bear likesays) ‚Üí Clarifying question ‚Üí Pitch ‚Üí Gauge interest ‚Üí Ask for meeting.

Here‚Äôs an example of what that would sound like for cold calls I make.


Opener: Hey John, it‚Äôs Oliver. How‚Äôre ya?

Probing Question: Awesome. Just curious - does your sales team currently track prospects/accounts that have visited the pricing page, but never actually booked a demo?

Clarifying Question: No? Well do you ever wonder how many prospects have visited your website, maybe have some interest, but never went through the hassle to book a demo themselves?

Pitch: Makes sense. Well we work with companies like yours that have a good amount of inbound demand, but want to convert even more prospects on the website.

will allow your sales team to view prospects on your website in real time, so that they can then live VIDEO call them. I mean‚Ä¶ imagine your speed to lead being literal SECONDS.

Gauge Interest: Just curious - does that sound intriguing at all?

Ask for the meeting: Sweet. Don‚Äôt want to take up your whole day here. Do you have a minute to chat on Tuesday next week?


Obviously, to be an effective cold caller, you need to be able to have fluid conversations - which means going off script at times.

However, I think this framework is a good way to get started/keep those conversations on track. Give it a try and tell me what you think!
